3633  } else if (hitPoint.h>max) {

3643  * this is why we compute the offset relative to the closest edge of the kern.*/

3655  * .............
3656  * min>>>>med>>>>max

3658  * negative kern: '.' means text, '<' means kern offset
3659  * ............................

3663  * There is a problem for such situation when there is efectively overlapping text.

3666  * It means that the best choice should be made according to the situation that occurs

3680  case synctex_node_type_math:
